/* Lore entry row → full data */
const LORE_ENTRIES = {
  'BloodyBirthdayCard': { title: 'You\'re 10!', byline: 'Love,', author: 'Mom and Dad', body: 'You’ve been growing so fast, I can’t believe it! You make Mommy and Daddy so proud. Happy Birthday Little One!', type: 'card' },
  'CRISPR': { title: 'World Health Organization On CRISPR', byline: 'Pandora\'s Box?', author: 'Buck Fernandez', body: 'The World Health Organization (WHO) has focused primarily on ethical and safety aspects of human genome editing, particularly concerning heritable changes and equitable access to such technologies. While their recommendations and discussions address the broader implications of human genome editing, they haven\'t specifically outlined a distinct set of limitations or regulations solely for the military applications of CRISPR, but rather approach the issue through the lens of dual-use technologies and ethical considerations.{/n}{/n}Dual-use and military concerns{/n} {/n}Dual Use Potential: CRISPR technology has a significant dual-use potential, meaning it can be employed for both beneficial purposes, like disease treatment and prevention, and for potentially harmful applications, including military uses.{/n} {/n}Potential Military Uses: Concerns exist about the possibility of using CRISPR to:{/n}{/n}- Create or manipulate pathogens for bioweapons{/n}- Engineer organisms to spread disease or cause other forms of harm{/n}- Develop "super soldiers" with enhanced physical or cognitive capabilitie.', type: 'newspaper' },
  'CommandOrder': { title: 'MEMORANDUM FOR  Joint Force Detachment 2', byline: 'Containment Procedures (CONPRO)', author: 'Command', body: 'At 0200 hrs, convoys will depart their respective quarantine zones and begin door-to-door assessments of all civilian housing. Any person showing minute symptoms will be taken into custody and placed on transport shuttles. Remaining personnel displaying zero symptoms are to be left in their homes. Mark the doors with the total number of people, the number of removed, the number remaining, and the date contact was made.{/n}{/n}Ensure Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) is worn at all times. Failure to adhere will result in severe administrative action.{/n}{/n}Transport shuttles will break away from the main contingent and proceed immediately to their standby locations for sanitization.', type: 'note' },
  'DocNote1': { title: 'Doc’s Journal Note', byline: '', author: '', body: '2 months into the trials, test results began to bear fruit. While the preventative measures initially sought were a complete failure, largely due to the perfect craftsmanship of the VX the experiments shifted from defensive capabilities to offensive applications.{/n}{/n}Test subjects did not last more than 72 hours before being declared deceased{/n}{/n}Within 3 to 16 hours, subjects began to exhibit reanimation. This was discovered when a contingent of technicians responsible for disposition reported movement inside the bodybags of several expired subjects.{/n}They called them "zombies". I laughed at the term. Something of a cinematic nomenclature to downplay the next stage of human evolution.{/n}{/n}We began importing more subjects from the prison, as well as "volunteers" from the local military forces who weren\'t well received within their respective roles. "An opportunity of a lifetime!" it was peddled. They won\'t be missed. No family, no one to write home to. Easier for us.', type: 'note' },
  'DocNote2': { title: 'Doc’s Journal Note #2', byline: '', author: '', body: '…has been overrun. I have absconded to the clean room for the time being until either the military deals with the lab breach, or the smart thing to do would be to vaporize the entire island, in which case this will be my last log. Knowing how "heroic" the government tries to be in saving research for later use, I believe this situation will escalate to a point they cannot control. The probability of escape is less than .01%, but that means there is a chance. I will try to reach the bridge blockade and make it to the mainland, but I\'m certain it won\'t be any safer there.', type: 'note' },
  'DyingLetter': { title: 'DyingLetter', byline: '', author: '', body: 'Whoever finds this, I had no choice. I had to shoot them, or else they would have turned into one of those things. Even now I can hear them clawing at the windows, shambling and scraping up against the house. I haven\'t made a sound in 2 days, but they know I\'m in here…and I know I can never get out. The smell from their bodies is filling the air and I don\'t have much supplies left. I\'m going to die in here…{/n}{/n}One of them scratched me as we were leaving our home. My arm is on fire and I\'ve not stopped sweating. I feel so tired all the time. Eating and drinking is becoming sickening, just thinking about it makes me want to vomit.', type: 'note' },
  'FinalContingencyPlan': { title: 'FinalContingencyPlan', byline: '', author: '', body: '…use of nuclear capabilities. This unequivocally falls into the realm of loss, theft, damage, destruction, misuse or compromise of ||REDACTED|| assets which can cause grave harm to the United States, will result in activation of the nuclear arsenal. Should the agency fail to reclaim the data from ||REDACTED||, authorization will be granted to the President in order to destroy any evidence or research which may be used by our adversaries, most notably ||REDACTED||. Collateral damage is expected and should not deter anyone from performing their duties.', type: 'unknown' },
  'News1': { title: 'Pharma Labs Land Grab', byline: 'Creating Jobs or Problems?', author: 'Buck Fernandez', body: 'Pharma Labs, the medical research company most recently under fire for adopting CRISPR technology, has recently purchased significant rural property in the northwest region of Anytown, with hopes of generating at least 200 new jobs initially and commercial growth for the local area valued at 450 million dollars over the next 2 years. Pharma Labs has also been a significant monetary donor to Mayor Huddson\'s most recent electoral campaign, and speculation is that a handshake deal has been made to allow the land purchase…', type: 'newspaper' },
  'News2': { title: 'Medical Research Turned Militant!', byline: 'Pharma Labs Captures Defense Contract', author: 'Buck Fernandez', body: 'Yesterday afternoon, top military officials proudly announced a contract negotiation was formally signed with Pharma Labs to help modernize medical military applications. Initial interviews as to what technology would be utilized and what modernization efforts were to take place were met with standoffish broad company lines focusing on battlefield survivability of deployed troops to hostile combat zones. This is no doubt in response to recent adversarial announcements shocking the world about using CRISPR technology to enhance soldier capabilities, elevating concerns as to how this gene manipulation has gone from science fiction to potential catastrophic disasters should the wrong people be using it.', type: 'newspaper' },
  'News3': { title: 'Questionable Quarantine?', byline: 'Huddson Occupied by Army Forces', author: 'Buck Fernandez', body: 'Mayor Winston Huddson declared a State of Emergency last Tuesday regarding the outbreak of an unknown strain of Bird Influenza which has ravaged the outlying towns. Within 24 hours, military Reserve forces have set up containment checkpoints across the region in order to contain the outbreak any further. All air traffic has been suspended into and out of Huddson Regional Airport, with hundreds stranded until the quarantine can be lifted. When reached for comment, Mayor Huddson assured that \'safety of our communities is the number one priority\', further reiterated cleaning standards, and to report any suspicious or malicious behavior to the nearest checkpoint supervisor.', type: 'newspaper' },
  'PreacherLastSermon': { title: 'PreacherLastSermon', byline: '', author: '', body: 'Revelation is upon us! My flock, do not fear what is coming. Embrace it! Know that you all will be judged, and those of you who are without sin will bask in the everafter! Those who have sinned, it is not too late for forgiveness. Let us walk among them. Let us take our journey together. They are our judges, they are our angels to guide us to the afterlife and continue to live on! We need not fear them. Join me, my children. Take each other hand in hand and let us walk together, now in life, as we will in death…', type: 'note' },
  'PrepperNote': { title: 'Prepper Note', byline: '', author: '', body: 'This is not a viral outbreak, this is government testing on OUR people! It\'s all out there for the world to see and NOTHING is being done! NOTHING! When will these people wake up and see what is going on…blinded by their own idiocy. Fortunately, I saw this coming years ago when they built that Pharma Lab so close to the prison. How stupid can they be that they can\'t see it? I\'ve kept my mouth shut, but maybe if I had said something, it would have at least made a difference. "Evacuation" they called it. I saw what they did…they loaded them onto buses, and took them out of sight and shot them all like dogs. Burned the bodies…easiest way to contain a situation is to remove the situation. But they won\'t find me here. I\'ll give it a few weeks, poke my head out, and see just how lost our world is…', type: 'note' },
};


